### Authentication Endpoints

### Register a new player
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "newplayer",
  "password": "password123",
  "email": "newplayer@example.com"
}

### Login with username
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "newplayer",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login with email
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "newplayer@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Login with sample player (admin)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "admin",
  "password": "admin123"
}

### Login with sample player (player1)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "player1",
  "password": "pass123"
}

### Get current user (replace <session-id> with actual session ID)
GET http://localhost:3000/api/auth/me
session-id: <session-id>

### Logout (replace <session-id> with actual session ID)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/logout
session-id: <session-id>

### Login with invalid credentials (should return 401)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "usernameOrEmail": "admin",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### Register with duplicate username (should return 409)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "password123",
  "email": "unique@example.com"
}

### Register with duplicate email (should return 409)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "uniqueuser",
  "password": "password123",
  "email": "admin@emberexchange.com"
}

### Register with short password (should return 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "123",
  "email": "test@example.com"
}

### Register with invalid email (should return 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "password": "password123",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}
